@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>SLATE</h1>
    <p class="lead">Slate is an easy to use scheduling application designed for restaurants and bars, featuring an automatic schedule creator.</p>
    <p><a href="http://asp.net" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Automatic Schedule Creator</h2>
        <p>
            Slate's powerful algorithm smartly creates schedules in seconds based off of just a few parameters entered in by you. 
            Taking into account availability, requests off, and more, making a schedule has never been more simple!
        </p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www.nfl.com">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Availability and Requests</h2>
        <p>Employees can easily adjust availabilities and submit request offs directly through Slate. After a manager's approval, everything is all taken care of! 
           The days of sticky notes everywhere are over.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www.nfl.com">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>View Your Schedule</h2>
        <p>Once created, managers and employees alike can view their various schedules. 
        Look at your own personal schedule, an entire week's schedule with all employees, 
        or view the employees that are working a given shift.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www.nfl.com">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
</div>